WEBVTT

00:03.916 --> 00:04.265
.

00:04.308 --> 00:06.354
- ♪ We wish you
a merry Christmas ♪

00:06.397 --> 00:08.965
♪ We wish you
a merry Christmas ♪

00:09.009 --> 00:10.532
♪ We wish you--

00:10.575 --> 00:13.013
♪

00:13.056 --> 00:15.972
Hello and Merry Christmas.

00:16.016 --> 00:19.367
I am Dwanta Claus, and during
this time of the year,

00:19.410 --> 00:21.847
I like to rip the sleeves
off my jacket

00:21.891 --> 00:23.762
and put on a hat with a bell,

00:23.806 --> 00:26.852
and I like to reflect back
on family, friends,

00:26.896 --> 00:31.944
and what makes
this holiday so very special.

00:31.988 --> 00:34.077
I love Christmas

00:34.121 --> 00:36.384
because it's all about
the three G's,

00:36.427 --> 00:41.606
gathering, giving,
and getting loose on eggnog.

00:41.650 --> 00:43.391
Now of course,
when you're a little kid,

00:43.434 --> 00:47.482
it's most about one thing:
the toys.

00:47.525 --> 00:48.831
I've been talking a lot about

00:48.874 --> 00:50.659
all the money troubles we had
in Hawaii,

00:50.702 --> 00:53.749
but Christmas 1983
was before all that,

00:53.792 --> 00:56.230
when we were still riding high
and I was about to learn

00:56.273 --> 00:58.536
a very valuable lesson
in gift-giving.

00:58.580 --> 01:01.104
- What are these cartoon shoes
on your feet?

01:01.148 --> 01:02.584
- Nice, right?

01:02.627 --> 01:04.716
They're from the Jane Seymour
for Mervyn's collection.

01:04.760 --> 01:06.849
I can't get over these.
I love them so much.

01:06.892 --> 01:08.242
They're so soft.

01:08.285 --> 01:10.200
Got them as a little Christmas
gift to myself.

01:10.244 --> 01:14.117
- Speaking of
Christmas gifts...

01:14.161 --> 01:16.163
as much
as I love the Radish Baby

01:16.206 --> 01:17.773
that you got me last year...

01:17.816 --> 01:19.383
[dramatic musical sting]
- [indistinct whispering]

01:19.427 --> 01:21.298
[echoing baby cry]

01:21.777 --> 01:23.909
- That doll is not right.

01:23.953 --> 01:26.738
- We knew it wasn't exactly
what I asked for,

01:26.782 --> 01:28.175
which is fine.

01:28.218 --> 01:32.179
But this year I made it
very easy for you.

01:32.222 --> 01:33.789
Here's a page
from the toy catalogue

01:33.832 --> 01:36.879
where I figured Skeletor,
the action figure I want,

01:36.922 --> 01:38.054
so you know what it looks like.

01:38.098 --> 01:39.360
- Why does he have muscles
on his body

01:39.403 --> 01:41.057
but not on his face?

01:41.101 --> 01:43.407
- Also, I called the store to
make sure that it was in stock,

01:43.451 --> 01:46.106
and they've put it aside
on a 48-hour hold.

01:46.149 --> 01:47.672
Here's a map, just in case.

01:47.716 --> 01:50.980
- [laughs] Okay.
Well, thank you, Dewey.

01:51.023 --> 01:53.591
I will make sure to pass all
this info along to Santa.

01:53.635 --> 01:55.506
- [laughs] Sure.

01:55.550 --> 01:56.594
- [laughs]

01:56.638 --> 01:59.293
- But it's on hold
under your name!

01:59.336 --> 02:01.686
- You put a lot of thought
into what gift you want.

02:01.730 --> 02:04.385
- Yeah, well, just between us,

02:04.428 --> 02:06.430
I kind of hate
that Radish Baby.

02:06.474 --> 02:08.867
Don't want another disaster
like that.

02:08.911 --> 02:10.217
[dramatic musical sting]

02:12.001 --> 02:13.002
Wait, where did he go?

02:13.045 --> 02:15.222
[echoing baby cry]

02:15.265 --> 02:17.354
- I hope you put
in the same amount of thought

02:17.398 --> 02:19.487
into the gift you get
for your mom.

02:19.530 --> 02:21.489
- What?
Adults give gifts to kids,

02:21.532 --> 02:22.664
not the other way around.

02:22.707 --> 02:24.927
- I see.
So you don't love your mother.

02:24.970 --> 02:26.276
- That's not what I'm saying.

02:26.320 --> 02:27.973
- Then why do you want
to make her feel unloved?

02:28.017 --> 02:29.279
- I don't.

02:29.323 --> 02:32.152
- Good,
then you will get her a gift.

02:32.195 --> 02:34.893
I'm glad you see it my way,
son.

02:34.937 --> 02:41.857
♪

02:41.900 --> 02:45.643
- I'm telling you, we need
to be making our own baby oil.

02:45.687 --> 02:46.992
That way we don't gotta
keep buying it.

02:47.036 --> 02:48.342
- Oh, no way, brother.

02:48.385 --> 02:50.953
I do not wanna know
how they get oil

02:50.996 --> 02:52.215
out of them babies.

02:52.259 --> 02:53.956
Just saying.
- Hey, Dad.

02:53.999 --> 02:55.479
- Dewey,
what are you doing here?

02:55.523 --> 02:56.785
- I need some advice.

02:56.828 --> 02:58.395
I don't know what
to get my mom for Christmas.

02:58.439 --> 02:59.831
- Join the club.
- Dewey.

02:59.875 --> 03:01.006
You wish to give
the gifts this year, huh?

03:01.050 --> 03:02.486
Not just receive them?

03:02.530 --> 03:04.053
You are like
a little Père Noel.

03:04.096 --> 03:05.315
I'm going to get you a robe.

03:05.359 --> 03:06.708
- You should get her a hot tub,
a big one,

03:06.751 --> 03:07.839
you know,
one that we can all fit in.

03:07.883 --> 03:09.841
- I have a box
of costume jewelry

03:09.885 --> 03:12.496
from my great aunt Deb
that I am looking to unload.

03:12.540 --> 03:14.672
- No, she does not want
any more jewelry.

03:14.716 --> 03:18.328
Last year I got us matching
diamond tennis bracelets.

03:18.372 --> 03:19.373
She said
it was irresponsible...

03:19.416 --> 03:21.026
- Pfft.
- Which is crazy.

03:21.070 --> 03:23.551
These are an investment.

03:24.813 --> 03:25.770
Oh, shoot.

03:25.814 --> 03:26.989
- Then I guess
the hot tub wins.

03:27.032 --> 03:28.164
- Oh, make sure it's a big one,

03:28.208 --> 03:29.339
you know, one
that we could all fit in.

03:29.383 --> 03:31.123
- I don't think
I can buy her a hot tub.

03:31.167 --> 03:32.255
- Wish I could help you, Dewey,

03:32.299 --> 03:34.344
but your mom is very hard
to shop for.

03:34.388 --> 03:35.998
- There's gotta be something
she'd like.

03:36.041 --> 03:38.479
I wish there was
a toy catalogue for adults.

03:38.522 --> 03:40.785
It'd be so much easier
if I could just see a bunch

03:40.829 --> 03:42.352
of gifts and choose one.

03:42.396 --> 03:45.355
- Dewey,
you just described a mall.

03:45.399 --> 03:47.836
- Oh, yeah, a mall.
[André chuckles]

03:47.879 --> 03:49.359
[bright music]

03:49.403 --> 03:51.448
But the mall was a bust.

03:51.492 --> 03:53.755
I wasn't seeing anything
I liked for my mom.

03:53.798 --> 03:55.626
However...

03:55.670 --> 03:57.062
Oh, candy.

03:57.106 --> 03:59.282
No. Gotta stay focused.

03:59.326 --> 04:00.283
I'm here for Mom.

04:00.327 --> 04:01.632
- Ho, ho, ho, ho.

04:01.676 --> 04:04.592
Ho, ho, ho, ho, ho.

04:04.635 --> 04:06.289
- [sighs]

04:06.333 --> 04:07.899
- Merry Christmas.

04:07.943 --> 04:10.293
Ho, ho, ho, ho, ho.

04:10.337 --> 04:12.339
[laughs] Well,
aren't you a little big

04:12.382 --> 04:14.123
to sit on Santa's lap?

04:14.166 --> 04:16.299
- Yeah, I'm not here for me.

04:16.343 --> 04:18.780
I need to get a gift
for my mom.

04:18.823 --> 04:22.305
- Well, uh,
what does your mom like?

04:22.349 --> 04:23.828
- Me.

04:23.872 --> 04:25.352
- Anything else?

04:25.395 --> 04:28.093
["Hark!
The Herald Angels Sing"]

04:28.137 --> 04:30.966
- ♪ Hark!
The Herald angels-- ♪

04:31.009 --> 04:32.141
- I got nothing.

04:32.184 --> 04:34.926
- Look, kid, my honest opinion,

04:34.970 --> 04:37.451
it doesn't really matter
what the gift is.

04:37.494 --> 04:40.149
What matters is how
it makes the person feel.

04:40.192 --> 04:42.238
Well, I'm sure
your mom's gonna like anything

04:42.282 --> 04:47.983
you give her, even if you just
slap googly eyes on a coconut.

04:48.026 --> 04:49.114
[rattling]

04:49.158 --> 04:50.551
- Nice.

04:50.594 --> 04:53.554
Might have overdone it
with the glitter paint.

04:53.597 --> 04:55.730
Gonna have to sun dry.

04:55.773 --> 04:56.905
[laughs]

04:59.777 --> 05:01.126
Ah! No!

05:01.170 --> 05:03.128
[dramatic music]

05:03.172 --> 05:07.002
[in slow motion]
No!

05:08.917 --> 05:10.527
No, no, no, no, no.

05:10.571 --> 05:13.138
[keys jingling]

05:13.182 --> 05:14.488
No!

05:19.928 --> 05:21.930
- I'm home.

05:24.236 --> 05:25.325
- Hi, Mom.

05:25.368 --> 05:27.196
- Were you doing crafts?
- No!

05:27.239 --> 05:30.155
I was just...
organizing the craft supplies.

05:30.199 --> 05:32.506
Someone put a glue stick inside
of the Magic Marker tray.

05:32.549 --> 05:33.985
People are animals.

05:34.029 --> 05:35.247
- What a great idea.

05:35.291 --> 05:36.640
Hey, if you're in the mood
for organizing,

05:36.684 --> 05:38.468
the linen closet is a disaster.

05:38.512 --> 05:40.383
- Yeah, I'll get on that later.

05:40.427 --> 05:42.342
I have an errand to run
for Grandma.

05:42.385 --> 05:43.691
- What errand?

05:43.734 --> 05:45.475
[suspenseful music]

05:45.519 --> 05:47.608
- Her--her mango shipment
was late

05:47.651 --> 05:49.000
so she asked me to go
to the store and get her some.

05:49.044 --> 05:50.350
Okay, bye.

05:50.393 --> 05:51.829
Smooth, right?

05:51.873 --> 05:55.877
So now I had a Christmas
disaster to clean up.

05:55.920 --> 05:58.445
[sighs]

05:58.488 --> 06:01.883
Yes, they're not sold-out.

06:01.926 --> 06:03.580
$15?

06:03.624 --> 06:06.888
What are these made out of,
gold doubloons?

06:06.931 --> 06:08.411
- Can I help you?

06:08.455 --> 06:12.328
You look too young to be here,
but too old to be lost.

06:12.372 --> 06:14.286
- Um, I need
to get these slippers,

06:14.330 --> 06:17.420
but I can't afford them.

06:17.464 --> 06:20.205
- Okay, well,
come back when you can.

06:20.249 --> 06:21.424
[laughs] Merry Christmas.

06:21.468 --> 06:22.686
- Wait.

06:22.730 --> 06:28.344
What if I gave you...

06:28.388 --> 06:32.174
four dollars and...

06:32.217 --> 06:34.872
this wallet?

06:34.916 --> 06:36.570
- No, sorry.

06:36.613 --> 06:39.268
- Look, Brig-itty.

06:39.311 --> 06:40.400
- Brigitte.

06:40.443 --> 06:42.750
- Bresheet.
- No.

06:42.793 --> 06:45.405
- I'm a businessman,
and you're a businesswoman.

06:45.448 --> 06:47.668
And as businesspeople,
we can both agree

06:47.711 --> 06:50.801
that $15 is way too much
for a pair of slippers.

06:50.845 --> 06:52.455
- [laughs] You're too young
to know how embarrassing

06:52.499 --> 06:55.502
this is for you,
but this is a Mervyn's.

06:55.545 --> 06:56.459
We don't haggle.

06:56.503 --> 06:58.548
[laughs]

06:58.592 --> 07:01.203
- I was gonna need
a Christmas miracle.

07:05.120 --> 07:05.337
.

07:05.381 --> 07:07.818
- I failed to get my mom
new slippers,

07:07.862 --> 07:09.820
and my frustrations
were at an all-time high.

07:09.864 --> 07:11.474
Hey!

07:11.518 --> 07:15.217
One of your colleagues gave me
some very bad advice earlier.

07:15.260 --> 07:17.393
He said my mom would be happy
with anything,

07:17.437 --> 07:20.222
so I made her a stupid coconut
with googly eyes,

07:20.265 --> 07:23.051
and then I dropped it
on her Jane Seymour slippers.

07:23.094 --> 07:24.879
But I can't replace them

07:24.922 --> 07:26.924
because Mervyn's
doesn't haggle.

07:26.968 --> 07:29.013
So now her entire Christmas
is ruined,

07:29.057 --> 07:32.277
and she's literally
a Christmas angel.

07:32.321 --> 07:36.499
- Maybe you should ask Santa
to bring you some slippers.

07:36.543 --> 07:38.109
Ho, ho, ho. [laughs]
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

07:38.153 --> 07:40.808
Enjoy your orange chicken.
- [chuckles]

07:40.851 --> 07:42.766
- My time had run out.

07:42.810 --> 07:45.465
It was Christmas morning
and I got my Skeletor,

07:45.508 --> 07:48.076
which made me feel even worse
about the slippers.

07:48.119 --> 07:49.947
- Back to socks like the rest
of us.

07:49.991 --> 07:51.514
What happened
to your poodle shoes?

07:51.558 --> 07:53.037
- Can't find them.

07:53.081 --> 07:55.083
I'm hoping they're buried
somewhere in the linen closet.

07:55.126 --> 07:57.738
- Last gift and it's for you.

07:57.781 --> 07:59.087
- But you already gave me
my gift,

07:59.130 --> 08:01.568
this, uh, lovely umbrella hat.

08:01.611 --> 08:04.092
- So my baby will always have
some shade.

08:04.135 --> 08:05.833
- Ah. [laughs]
- But this one's not from me.

08:05.876 --> 08:07.312
It's from Dewey.

08:07.356 --> 08:08.705
- It is?

08:08.749 --> 08:11.403
- Oh, Dewey, you didn't have
to get me anything.

08:11.447 --> 08:13.580
That's so sweet.

08:13.623 --> 08:15.495
Aww.

08:15.538 --> 08:16.713
- What is it?

08:16.757 --> 08:19.063
- It's a little coconut
with googly eyes.

08:19.107 --> 08:21.283
Look at his little hat.

08:21.326 --> 08:25.287
Dewey, I love it so much.

08:25.330 --> 08:28.333
- God damn, I could've
just been making coconuts.

08:28.377 --> 08:30.292
- Okay, let's eat breakfast.

08:30.335 --> 08:33.774
Mr. Coconut gets
a special place on the table.

08:33.817 --> 08:35.993
- Good job, Dewey.

08:39.693 --> 08:42.652
[soft mysterious music]

08:42.696 --> 08:49.572
♪

08:53.620 --> 08:55.665
- The slippers.

08:55.709 --> 08:59.147
♪

08:59.190 --> 09:01.628
Mom, I found your slippers.

09:01.671 --> 09:03.064
So to this very day...
- Oh!

09:03.107 --> 09:05.632
- I don't know if that was
Santa Claus or not,

09:05.675 --> 09:09.157
but I do know that I am
a believer in Christmas magic

09:09.200 --> 09:11.507
and the gift of giving.

09:11.551 --> 09:13.640
Now that Christmas in Hawaii
was the first time

09:13.683 --> 09:16.947
I ever experienced the joy
of giving a gift.

09:16.991 --> 09:18.340
And from then on,

09:18.383 --> 09:23.301
I was absolutely obsessed
with it.

09:23.345 --> 09:25.826
The coconut with googly eyes
became a tradition

09:25.869 --> 09:27.392
for me and my mom.

09:27.436 --> 09:29.177
I still make her one
every year.

09:29.220 --> 09:31.440
- Hey, can that one be
from both of us?

09:31.483 --> 09:33.181
I have no idea what to get her.

09:33.224 --> 09:36.445
- Sorry, Dad.
These coconuts are all mine.

09:36.488 --> 09:38.665
- Dewey, I need you to come
to work with me today.

09:38.708 --> 09:40.492
- Why?

09:40.536 --> 09:41.798
- My client Suzanne is hosting
a big Christmas party tonight.

09:41.842 --> 09:43.321
I need extra help with,
you know, cleaning,

09:43.365 --> 09:44.758
getting everything set up
for her.

09:44.801 --> 09:46.977
- Hey, at least you don't have
to go to the party.

09:47.021 --> 09:48.588
Probably boring as hell.

09:48.631 --> 09:50.590
Don't include me
in your conversation.

09:50.633 --> 09:52.635
No, I don't ski.

09:52.679 --> 09:54.463
- We're going to the party
as well, you too.

09:54.506 --> 09:55.638
- I love how you just assume

09:55.682 --> 09:57.074
that I have nothing
to do all day

09:57.118 --> 09:59.381
and free to come to work
with you and go to a party.

09:59.424 --> 10:02.123
- Do you have something
to do today?

10:02.166 --> 10:03.385
- No.

10:03.428 --> 10:06.388
[mellow holiday music]

10:06.736 --> 10:08.303
Bathrooms are all cleaned
and stocked

10:08.346 --> 10:09.826
with Christmas tree hand soaps.
- [chuckles]

10:09.870 --> 10:11.959
- Which I'm pretty sure
permanently stained my hands.

10:12.002 --> 10:13.700
- [gasps] Oh.
[door closes]

10:13.743 --> 10:15.049
- How's everything going?

10:15.092 --> 10:17.660
- We're all done.
- Oh, good.

10:17.704 --> 10:19.009
Well, before you go,

10:19.053 --> 10:20.663
I just wanted
to give you a little something.

10:20.707 --> 10:22.447
- Damn, that's not
a little anything.

10:22.491 --> 10:24.275
- Oh, you didn't have
to give us a gift.

10:24.319 --> 10:25.929
- I just wanted to thank you
for all your hard work

10:25.973 --> 10:27.235
this year.

10:27.278 --> 10:28.584
Go ahead. Open it.

10:34.155 --> 10:38.202
- Oh!
Oh, wow, an ice cream maker.

10:38.246 --> 10:40.291
Oh, this is so nice.
Thank you so much.

10:40.335 --> 10:41.728
- Yeah, thanks.

10:41.771 --> 10:44.382
We got you something too, uh,
just left it at home.

10:44.426 --> 10:45.949
We'll bring it to the party.
- Mm-hmm.

10:45.993 --> 10:47.821
- Aw, you got me a present?

10:47.864 --> 10:48.865
That is so sweet.

10:48.909 --> 10:50.258
I love presents.

10:50.301 --> 10:51.738
See you tonight?

10:53.435 --> 10:55.263
- We didn't get her a present.

10:55.306 --> 10:57.744
- We'll figure something out.

10:57.787 --> 11:00.616
That started my next lesson
in gift-giving.

11:00.660 --> 11:02.618
As a teenager, I thought
it was pretty simple.

11:02.662 --> 11:04.533
You get a gift,
and you give a gift.

11:04.576 --> 11:06.796
But it's not always
that cut and dry.

11:06.840 --> 11:09.320
- He's unable to get up now.
A nice--

11:09.364 --> 11:10.713
- Rocky, get up.

11:10.757 --> 11:11.888
We need to go to the mall
and get Suzanne a gift.

11:11.932 --> 11:13.368
- A gift?

11:13.411 --> 11:15.675
But she's your boss.
You don't gift up.

11:15.718 --> 11:17.502
Did I ever get a gift
for Vince?

11:17.546 --> 11:19.026
- You never got a gift
for Vince?

11:19.069 --> 11:22.159
- The man owns a T. rex skull.
The hell can I buy him?

11:22.203 --> 11:23.291
- Dewey promised Suzanne
a gift,

11:23.334 --> 11:24.596
so now we have
to get her a gift,

11:24.640 --> 11:25.989
and it needs to be something
as nice

11:26.033 --> 11:27.817
as this beautiful
ice cream maker.

11:27.861 --> 11:29.471
♪

11:29.514 --> 11:31.342
Come on.
The party's in a couple hours.

11:31.386 --> 11:33.301
♪

11:33.344 --> 11:34.868
- [growls]

11:37.000 --> 11:37.174
.

11:37.218 --> 11:40.612
- Okay, we need a nice gift
that costs almost nothing.

11:40.656 --> 11:42.919
- Our prayers
have been answered.

11:42.963 --> 11:45.748
- You wanna enter
a radio contest for an ATV?

11:45.792 --> 11:47.750
- It's free, ain't it?

11:47.794 --> 11:49.273
- I say we just go
to Le Chic Boutique

11:49.317 --> 11:51.014
and buy the least expensive
thing we can find.

11:51.058 --> 11:52.842
We can get the store to wrap it
so it looks fancy.

11:52.886 --> 11:54.061
- Sounds like a plan.
- Come on, Rocky.

11:54.104 --> 11:56.106
- And go!
[air horn blasts]

11:56.150 --> 11:58.718
- Rocky.

11:58.761 --> 12:00.502
- Oh, trust me.
I can win this thing.

12:00.545 --> 12:03.505
- [sighs]
We'll see you at home.

12:03.548 --> 12:04.593
- Fans of wrestling, anyone?

12:04.636 --> 12:06.334
- Eh, mm.

12:06.377 --> 12:08.771
♪

12:08.815 --> 12:12.470
- Ooh, so graceful.

12:12.514 --> 12:14.429
$300?

12:14.472 --> 12:15.778
What, does it grant wishes?

12:15.822 --> 12:17.301
- This is the cheapest thing
I could find.

12:17.345 --> 12:19.042
- [sighs]

12:19.086 --> 12:21.262
"You wash... I'll die."

12:21.305 --> 12:22.916
- Instead of "I'll dry."

12:22.959 --> 12:24.787
[laughs]
- This is no use.

12:24.831 --> 12:27.311
Everything in here
is too expensive.

12:27.355 --> 12:29.139
- You know, I could...

12:29.183 --> 12:30.358
- What?

12:30.401 --> 12:31.489
- [whispering]
I could get us something

12:31.533 --> 12:32.577
without paying for it.

12:32.621 --> 12:34.275
- How?
Do you have a coupon?

12:34.318 --> 12:37.104
- No. I mean...

12:37.147 --> 12:39.628
- Stealing?

12:39.671 --> 12:40.803
At Christmastime?

12:40.847 --> 12:43.327
- Certainly not anymore.

12:43.371 --> 12:44.807
Should probably pay for this.
They're definitely gonna think

12:44.851 --> 12:45.808
we stole something.

12:45.852 --> 12:47.549
- [sighs]

12:47.592 --> 12:49.681
Well, at least it's cheap.

12:49.725 --> 12:50.857
[gasps]

12:50.900 --> 12:52.162
- What?
- I know what her gift can be.

12:52.206 --> 12:54.686
We can make ice cream
for Suzanne.

12:54.730 --> 12:56.384
There's no better feeling
than knowing

12:56.427 --> 12:58.299
that someone really appreciates
the gift you give them, right?

12:58.342 --> 13:00.170
- That's what
that gasp was for?

13:00.214 --> 13:02.303
I thought you saw a rat.
- [groans]

13:02.346 --> 13:04.653
There's so many parts
to assemble.

13:04.696 --> 13:07.787
First it says
we need the driver ring?

13:07.830 --> 13:08.875
[pieces clattering]

13:08.918 --> 13:11.703
- Wait, this is open?
- Yeah.

13:11.747 --> 13:12.704
And what's this on the manual?

13:12.748 --> 13:15.098
Is this red wine?

13:15.142 --> 13:16.796
Suzanne must have used this.

13:16.839 --> 13:18.145
- This is a regift?

13:18.188 --> 13:19.668
She didn't put any thought
into this.

13:19.711 --> 13:22.192
But all she did was wrap up
something she didn't want.

13:22.236 --> 13:25.065
That's not even a gift.
That's decorated trash.

13:25.108 --> 13:27.110
[mysterious holiday music]

13:27.154 --> 13:29.852
- And that's exactly
what we're gonna give her.

13:29.896 --> 13:31.201
- Two contestants left.

13:31.245 --> 13:34.204
Who's gonna win?
- Aw, you gotta tinkle winkle?

13:34.248 --> 13:35.815
There's a bathroom
right over there.

13:35.858 --> 13:38.339
[laughs]

13:38.382 --> 13:39.296
- Whoa!
- Ah.

13:39.340 --> 13:40.863
- Rocky Johnson!

13:40.907 --> 13:42.734
Can I get your autograph?
- Hell yeah.

13:42.778 --> 13:43.779
- We have a winner!

13:43.823 --> 13:46.695
[air horn blows]
[applause]

13:46.738 --> 13:48.566
- Aw, man!

13:48.610 --> 13:50.786
[sighs]
Price of fame.

13:50.830 --> 13:52.744
Come on.

13:52.788 --> 13:54.094
[doorbell rings]

13:55.486 --> 13:56.966
- Hi!
- You made it.

13:57.010 --> 13:58.141
- We did.
[laughs]

13:58.185 --> 13:59.360
Merry Christmas.
- [laughing] Oh.

13:59.403 --> 14:01.753
You didn't have
to get me anything.

14:01.797 --> 14:03.407
Oh.

14:03.451 --> 14:05.496
Oh.

14:05.540 --> 14:08.717
Uh...I don't wash dishes.

14:08.760 --> 14:10.893
- Well, maybe you could spill
some red wine on it

14:10.937 --> 14:12.112
and give it to someone else.

14:12.155 --> 14:13.417
[laughs]

14:13.461 --> 14:14.941
- Oh.

14:14.984 --> 14:17.291
Thank you.
Come in, come in.

14:17.334 --> 14:19.423
Is your husband coming?
- Oh, he had to work late.

14:19.467 --> 14:21.425
- Oh.

14:21.469 --> 14:23.558
- I never forgot
that negative experience

14:23.601 --> 14:25.908
with my mom's rich boss.

14:25.952 --> 14:27.431
So when I got to the point
in my life

14:27.475 --> 14:30.870
where I had a little more
than 7 bucks in my pocket,

14:30.913 --> 14:34.525
I wanted to share it and try
to give people the best gifts

14:34.569 --> 14:36.136
they ever got.

14:36.919 --> 14:38.529
Like I remember
this one Christmas

14:38.573 --> 14:40.705
at Mick Foley's house.

14:40.749 --> 14:43.447
Now there's one thing
you should know about Mick.

14:43.491 --> 14:44.971
He loves Christmas.

14:45.014 --> 14:46.929
- God, I love Christmas.

14:46.973 --> 14:49.540
- Every year he would host
a Christmas party for the guys

14:49.584 --> 14:51.847
and we would all do
our Secret Santa.

14:51.891 --> 14:55.024
- All right,
time for Secret Santa.

14:55.068 --> 14:56.678
Dwayne,
since this is your first time

14:56.721 --> 14:59.681
at my Christmas soirée,
you get to open first.

14:59.724 --> 15:01.291
Welcome, brother.
- Thanks, Mick.

15:01.335 --> 15:03.337
- Oh, it's not from me.
It's from your Secret Santa.

15:03.380 --> 15:04.729
- Oh, okay.

15:04.773 --> 15:06.818
[inhales deeply]

15:06.862 --> 15:09.821
Oh, wow.
Nice.

15:09.865 --> 15:11.606
My dad used
to have one just like it.

15:11.649 --> 15:13.303
Who was this from?
- Me.

15:13.347 --> 15:15.784
I almost got it engraved
to say "Never shuts up"...

15:15.827 --> 15:17.742
But it's Christmas.
[laughter]

15:17.786 --> 15:18.787
- Thank you.

15:18.830 --> 15:21.137
- This one's for...

15:21.181 --> 15:23.661
[gasps] Me.
[laughs]

15:23.705 --> 15:26.012
- When I drew Mick's name
for Secret Santa,

15:26.055 --> 15:27.578
I knew I had to go all-out,

15:27.622 --> 15:29.711
so I got him
an incredible gift.

15:29.754 --> 15:32.975
- Wow. This is...
[Dwayne chuckles]

15:33.019 --> 15:34.324
What am I looking at here?

15:34.368 --> 15:36.457
- Well, the coconut
is a family tradition.

15:36.500 --> 15:38.546
I make one
for my mom every year.

15:38.589 --> 15:40.548
It used to be
he was the only gift,

15:40.591 --> 15:43.551
but now he brings other gifts
with him.

15:43.594 --> 15:44.726
And he's brought you

15:44.769 --> 15:46.946
an all-inclusive
first-class trip

15:46.989 --> 15:48.121
to the Bahamas.

15:48.164 --> 15:49.949
You and your family
leave tomorrow

15:49.992 --> 15:51.211
for the weekend.
[people murmuring]

15:51.254 --> 15:52.864
Merry Christmas! [laughs]

15:52.908 --> 15:55.693
Or at least I thought
it was an incredible gift.

15:55.737 --> 15:57.913
Turns out I had another lesson
to learn.

15:57.957 --> 16:00.916
- Wow, that's very generous.
Thank you.

16:03.049 --> 16:04.964
All right, who's next?

16:05.007 --> 16:07.488
- Not quite the reaction
I was expecting.

16:09.577 --> 16:09.794
.

16:09.838 --> 16:11.622
- Hey, do you guys think
it was weird,

16:11.666 --> 16:12.580
Mick's reaction to my gift?

16:12.623 --> 16:14.060
It seemed like
he didn't like it.

16:14.103 --> 16:15.626
- I mean, he said thank you.

16:15.670 --> 16:17.193
What more could you ask for,
right?

16:17.237 --> 16:19.587
[people chattering]

16:20.718 --> 16:22.546
- Ho, ho, ho, ho!
- Hey, Santa.

16:22.590 --> 16:24.896
- Hey.
Excited for your trip?

16:24.940 --> 16:27.856
This time tomorrow,
you'll be sitting by the pool.

16:27.899 --> 16:29.858
Actually, this time tomorrow
you'll be on your layover

16:29.901 --> 16:32.339
in Charlotte,
but it's a nice airport.

16:32.382 --> 16:34.254
- Yeah, um, listen, man.

16:34.297 --> 16:35.864
I'm sorry, but I can't go.

16:35.907 --> 16:38.562
It's just I've a thing tomorrow
I can't miss.

16:38.606 --> 16:41.043
But I love the coconut.
- Oh, my bad.

16:41.087 --> 16:44.090
I, uh--I thought since we had
the next few days off work

16:44.133 --> 16:46.962
you'd be okay
to travel on the weekend.

16:47.006 --> 16:49.051
- Wish I could, but hey,
why don't you go?

16:49.095 --> 16:52.185
Have some fun in the sun?
- [laughs]

16:52.228 --> 16:54.883
I felt like I had
ruined Christmas for Mick.

16:54.926 --> 16:57.364
A bad gift is worse
than no gift at all,

16:57.407 --> 17:00.541
so I was determined
to get him something better.

17:00.584 --> 17:03.109
Hey, it turns out
Mick can't make the trip.

17:03.152 --> 17:05.720
So how 'bout you trade me
your Secret Santa gift,

17:05.763 --> 17:07.591
I'll give it to Mick,
and you can go to the Bahamas.

17:07.635 --> 17:09.419
- Ah, I don't know, man.

17:09.463 --> 17:10.725
You know,
I'm just not a huge fan

17:10.768 --> 17:12.205
of flying over water.

17:12.248 --> 17:14.207
- ♪ Tra-la-la-la-la,
la-la-la, la-la-la ♪

17:14.250 --> 17:16.644
♪ La-la-la-la-la

17:16.687 --> 17:18.472
- Hey, Undertaker,

17:18.515 --> 17:20.909
wanna trade me that--
- No.

17:20.952 --> 17:22.258
- Hey, big head.

17:22.302 --> 17:24.347
- Triple H.
- I'll trade you.

17:24.391 --> 17:25.957
I'm not a robe guy.

17:26.001 --> 17:28.525
Thanks to my father who could
never find the belt for his.

17:28.569 --> 17:30.049
- Okay.

17:30.092 --> 17:32.399
[upbeat music]

17:32.442 --> 17:34.053
Hey, Mick.

17:34.096 --> 17:35.750
Merry Christmas.

17:35.793 --> 17:37.447
- Is this for me?
You already got me a gift.

17:37.491 --> 17:38.579
- Yeah, but I traded it.

17:38.622 --> 17:40.102
I'm sorry, man.

17:40.146 --> 17:42.191
I know how much
you love Christmas,

17:42.235 --> 17:44.063
and I ruined your Secret Santa.

17:44.106 --> 17:47.327
I just wanted
to get you something great.

17:47.370 --> 17:50.025
- Hey, come with me.
I wanna show you something.

17:50.069 --> 17:51.418
- Okay.

17:51.461 --> 17:54.203
- You know how in matches
I fall onto thumbtacks?

17:54.247 --> 17:55.422
- Of course.

17:55.465 --> 17:56.858
You're the most hardcore
out of all of us.

17:56.901 --> 17:59.556
- Well, this is every tack

17:59.600 --> 18:01.950
I've ever pulled out
of my back after a match,

18:01.993 --> 18:05.606
fused together to form
a life-sized Tori Amos.

18:05.649 --> 18:08.217
- Wow, I got a lot of questions
about this.

18:08.261 --> 18:10.350
- I had it made as a reminder
of how far I'm willing to go

18:10.393 --> 18:11.916
to give a good show.

18:11.960 --> 18:14.267
And as a reminder
of how much I love Tori Amos.

18:14.310 --> 18:15.616
- Has Tori seen this?

18:15.659 --> 18:16.921
And if so, is she flattered

18:16.965 --> 18:18.836
or is this a restraining order
situation?

18:18.880 --> 18:21.230
- I love that feeling, man,

18:21.274 --> 18:24.146
knowing that you gave it
absolutely everything you had

18:24.190 --> 18:26.801
and hearing
how the crowd loves it.

18:26.844 --> 18:28.890
Giving is what
makes me the happiest.

18:28.933 --> 18:30.631
I don't even like
receiving gifts.

18:30.674 --> 18:32.894
- Oh, I get that.
I mean, I'm only wearing this

18:32.937 --> 18:34.983
because I don't wanna hurt
Stone Cold's feelings.

18:35.026 --> 18:36.637
- Yeah, giving gifts to adults

18:36.680 --> 18:38.639
who can buy whatever they want,
it's no fun.

18:38.682 --> 18:40.423
You're just swapping stuff.

18:40.467 --> 18:43.948
That's why I drop toys off at
this youth center every year.

18:43.992 --> 18:46.473
That's a real Christmas gift,

18:46.516 --> 18:47.909
donating your time
and resources

18:47.952 --> 18:50.564
to help people less fortunate.

18:50.607 --> 18:52.392
I love putting on a show
for those kids,

18:52.435 --> 18:54.394
seeing their faces light up.

18:54.437 --> 18:57.005
- And I thought André the Giant
was Christmas personified.

18:57.048 --> 18:58.093
- Oh, ho, ho.

18:58.137 --> 18:59.181
- You give him a run
for his money.

18:59.225 --> 19:00.617
- [laughing] Wow.

19:00.661 --> 19:02.793
- But you know what?
That toy drive sounds awesome.

19:02.837 --> 19:04.230
I'd love to come with.

19:04.273 --> 19:06.667
- I'd love your help with it,
but you can't come.

19:06.710 --> 19:09.191
Heels can't do charity events
for kids.

19:09.235 --> 19:11.062
- [sighs]
- Good guys only.

19:11.106 --> 19:12.673
- Right.

19:12.716 --> 19:15.023
But do you know what would make
for a good show?

19:15.066 --> 19:16.242
- Huh?

19:16.285 --> 19:18.896
You kids must've been real good
this year

19:18.940 --> 19:21.856
'cause the big guy sent lots
of presents!

19:21.899 --> 19:23.292
[cheers and applause]
Yay!

19:23.336 --> 19:25.642
- There was one heel
that could be at the event.

19:25.686 --> 19:27.470
- Well, well, well.

19:27.514 --> 19:28.776
[kids whispering]

19:28.819 --> 19:30.430
What do we have here?

19:30.473 --> 19:31.953
The ultimate heel.

19:31.996 --> 19:34.216
- Oh, no! It's the Grinch!

19:34.260 --> 19:37.219
[all booing]

19:37.263 --> 19:39.047
- You better get out of here,
Grinch,

19:39.090 --> 19:41.528
before Stone Cold
sticks his mistletoe

19:41.571 --> 19:43.051
right up your chimney.

19:43.094 --> 19:46.054
- I'm stealing all the toys
I can find

19:46.097 --> 19:50.493
and giving the People's Elbow
to every Santa I see.

19:50.537 --> 19:52.887
[kids screaming]

19:52.930 --> 19:55.237
- The only thing
you're getting, Grinch,

19:55.281 --> 19:56.543
is a whuppin'!

19:56.586 --> 19:58.197
- Yeah?
[both grunting]

19:58.240 --> 19:59.589
[kids cheering]

19:59.633 --> 20:00.764
[Stevie Wonder's
"What Christmas Means to Me"]

20:00.808 --> 20:02.636
- ♪ Lots of mistletoe

20:02.679 --> 20:04.072
- [groans]

20:04.115 --> 20:05.987
- ♪ Lots of snow and ice
- Ooh!

20:06.030 --> 20:06.901
Ah!

20:06.944 --> 20:08.250
- ♪ Everywhere we go

20:08.294 --> 20:09.251
- Merry Christmas, Mick.

20:09.295 --> 20:11.122
- Back at you, buddy.

20:11.166 --> 20:12.472
[kids cheering]

20:12.515 --> 20:15.126
- And so it turns out
the best gift advice

20:15.170 --> 20:17.912
I ever got was
from that mall Santa

20:17.955 --> 20:20.915
all those years ago in Hawaii.

20:20.958 --> 20:23.091
It's not about
what the gift is.

20:23.134 --> 20:25.833
It's about
how it makes the person feel.

20:25.876 --> 20:27.748
Whether they're a fancy gift,

20:27.791 --> 20:29.010
or a homemade gift,

20:29.053 --> 20:31.055
or even just a simple gesture,

20:31.099 --> 20:34.363
gifts are my love language.

20:34.407 --> 20:36.539
[soft Christmas music]

20:36.583 --> 20:38.019
This one's a pepper mill

20:38.062 --> 20:40.587
for my good friend,
Stanley Tucci.

20:40.630 --> 20:42.153
Merry Christmas, Tooch.

20:44.373 --> 20:48.159
[exhales] Well, I really
enjoyed spending this time

20:48.203 --> 20:49.378
with you all.

20:49.422 --> 20:51.380
And don't forget
on Christmas Eve

20:51.424 --> 20:54.383
to leave out some tequila,
some sandwiches,

20:54.427 --> 20:57.778
and some cookies
for old Dwanta Claus here.

20:57.821 --> 21:00.781
But hold the sandwiches,
and hold the cookies.

21:00.824 --> 21:01.869
That's right.

21:01.912 --> 21:04.045
Dwanta's gettin' loaded.

21:04.088 --> 21:06.003
[laughs] Good night, everyone.

21:06.047 --> 21:09.398
Merry Christmas,
Mele Kalikimaka,

21:09.442 --> 21:13.663
and happy holidays to you
and your families.

21:13.707 --> 21:15.143
[blows kiss]

21:15.186 --> 21:16.971
♪

21:17.014 --> 21:18.407
And for all
the little kids out there

21:18.451 --> 21:19.843
that might wanna
get their parents

21:19.887 --> 21:23.717
the perfect gift,
don't worry.

21:23.760 --> 21:26.720
They'll love it
no matter what.
